Docker - is executable software app that allows developers and ops team
         build, deploy and run  light weight applications to a sufficient environment.

Docker registry - Repository that contains docker images

image - A executable package which contains application src code, dependencies
        and config files to create a docker container.

        docker pull image:version
        - pulls an image from docker registry

Docker container - is a running docker
                   - To start docker container you run the docker image

                   docker run nginx:1.23

                      - start an instance of nginx container but blocks the terminal

                   docker run -d nginx:1.23
                     
                      - Start docker container in a detached state(does not block the terminal)
                      - To see logs from this background container.

                       docker log container_id